tweets.author: IHPA
tweets.text:
Health policy shapes everything from your doctor’s office to your pharmacy counter.

But trying to influence it? Feels like navigating a maze.

IHPA is your map through it all. Follow us today to start finding your way through.

thread_replies.author: IHPA
thread_replies.text:
DECODED: Spread Pricing

What they say: “Pharmacy Benefit Managers negotiate discounts to lower your drug costs.”

What it really means:
PBMs pocket the difference between what they bill your health plan and what they pay the pharmacy — that’s called spread pricing. You pay more,

What they say… vs. what it really means.

tweets.author: IHPA
tweets.text:
Healthcare isn’t expensive by accident.

From prescription prices to insurance premiums, nearly every dollar you spend is shaped by a policy decision—often influenced by powerful special interests.

tweets.author: IHPA
tweets.text:
At IHPA, we follow the money, decode the fine print, and ask the hard questions.

Because patients deserve to know why care costs what it does.
